cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper is about deep learning-based methods for single image super-resolution (SISR), which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization objectives and neural network architectures used in SISR, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper mentions comparisons of different methods from various perspectives, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
